some other aspects of the question and shall ask her to communicate with you.

There is something else I would like to mention: I have received no statement of accounts from you on either of the two dates on which they were due. I would appreciate receiving one now.





Sincerely yours,

Vladimir Nabokov





TO: GRAHAM GREENE

CC, 1 p.

Ithaca, N.Y.





31 December 1956

Dear Mr. Greene,

From various friends I keep receiving heart-warming reports on your kindness to my books. This is New Yea